an absence of a girlfriend

263
00:16:03,966 --> 00:16:06,386
does not necessarily mean
I'm willing to

264
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:08,200
give her my number.

265
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:11,633
Why are you laughing?

266
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:17,000
I just thought, you have
an iron defense against women.

267
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,786
Why are you looking at me
like that?

268
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:34,500
I've never seen you
with such a big smile.

269
00:16:38,266 --> 00:16:40,720
Why the straight face again?

270
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,086
Smile like just before.

271
00:16:42,166 --> 00:16:44,386
It's nicer when you smile.

272
00:16:44,466 --> 00:16:46,200
Come on, please?

273
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:49,233
I'll smile when I want to,
thank you.

274
00:17:10,533 --> 00:17:12,320
Thank you for taking me home.

275
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,553
It's nothing.

276
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:15,000
I'll see you on Monday.

277
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:33,500
(Raon Drive-in Theater)

278
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:35,453
Ah, so you saw a movie today!

279
00:17:35,533 --> 00:17:36,600
With who?

280
00:17:38,266 --> 00:17:39,853
You don't have to know.

281
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:42,500
Why? But I want to know.

282
00:17:43,266 --> 00:17:47,620
Man, I never thought I'll ever
see you go on a date!

283
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:48,953
It wasn't a date.

284
00:17:49,033 --> 00:17:50,320
Whatever!

285
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:51,653
You never watch movies,

286
00:17:51,733 --> 00:17:53,453
so you going to a theater is
saying something.

287
00:17:53,533 --> 00:17:55,720
I said, it's not like that.

288
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:56,986
We were only studying.

289
00:17:57,066 --> 00:17:59,520
What? Study?

290
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:02,586
My secretary said she wanted to
study law,

291
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:04,353
so we watched a film
about law together.

292
00:18:04,433 --> 00:18:05,566
To study.

293
00:18:06,733 --> 00:18:08,433
Do you think that makes sense?

294
00:18:10,466 --> 00:18:11,820
Well, do you think
this makes sense,

295
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:12,820
leeching off me at my place?

296
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:14,466
Isn't it about time that
you move out?

297
00:18:15,466 --> 00:18:17,553
Fine. We'll just
leave it at this today.

298
00:18:17,633 --> 00:18:18,766
Get some rest, then.

299
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:20,866
Mr. Kwon Jung-rok,

300
00:18:21,533 --> 00:18:23,933
who went to the theater to
study law.

301
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:41,720
Mr. Kwon,

302
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:45,086
thank you for
all your teaching today.

303
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:46,766
Good night, then.

304
00:18:55,500 --> 00:18:56,500
(Mr. Kwon Jung-rok)

305
00:18:58,633 --> 00:19:00,966
Sweet dreams to you too,
Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

306
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,733
You're not getting out?
Hey, I'm going to smash this!

307
00:19:09,666 --> 00:19:11,420
You can talk with me.

308
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,653
I'm her lawyer.

309
00:19:13,733 --> 00:19:14,920
What...

310
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:17,120
Why did he help me back then?

311
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:19,086
Why? Why?

312
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:20,666
Because he was worried about me?

313
00:19:23,866 --> 00:19:25,420
Well done.

314
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:28,100
Well done, Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

315
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,920
He could've just
returned the scarf,

316
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:36,466
so why did he have to
wrap it around my neck? Why?

317
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:43,720
And what was with that big smile?

318
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,920
Is it because of me?

319
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,233
Oh, my goodness!

320
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:51,500
I mean, come on!
Why did he smile like that?

321
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:08,366
Good morning, Mr. Kwon.

322
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:21,153
Mr. Kwon, your suit today is
really stu...

323
00:20:21,233 --> 00:20:23,586
Hello, Yoon-seo.

324
00:20:23,666 --> 00:20:24,920
Hi, good morning!

325
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,133
- Good morning.
- Hello.

326
00:20:29,266 --> 00:20:30,453
Oh, Yoon-seo.

327
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:32,486
The elevator can get crowded
in the morning.

328
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:34,220
- Will you be okay?
- Sorry?

329
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:37,486
I'm just worried that
people will recognize you.

330
00:20:37,566 --> 00:20:39,753
What, can you tell?

331
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:41,366
Of course I can tell. Of co...

332
00:20:43,366 --> 00:20:45,020
Or is it just me?

333
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:47,420
But then again, I would
recognize you in a niqab.

334
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,420
Why?

335
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:50,100
Because I'm your...

336
00:20:52,533 --> 00:20:54,033
...CEO.

337
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,066
Of course.

338
00:20:57,900 --> 00:21:00,520
Do you wait for me every
morning for me or something?

339
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:02,286
Because it feels like
I always bump into you here.

340
00:21:02,366 --> 00:21:03,920
Right?

341
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,353
We always bump into each other
in the elevator, huh?

342
00:21:06,433 --> 00:21:07,853
I was always
curious about that, too.

343
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:10,420
I guess that's destiny.

344
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:12,353
You, Mr. Kwon,

345
00:21:12,433 --> 00:21:14,166
and Yoon-seo, too.

346
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:16,266
Destiny!

347
00:21:16,966 --> 00:21:18,520
Right, Yoon-seo?

348
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,200
- Right.
- Right?

349
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:22,400
Excuse me.

350
00:21:23,666 --> 00:21:25,300
Ah, Director Lee Chung-jae.

351
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:28,033
He's a TV show director!

352
00:21:30,433 --> 00:21:32,020
What, you need one more?

353
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:34,486
What's this emergency
meeting about?

354
00:21:34,566 --> 00:21:35,753
Well, it's nothing really.

355
00:21:35,833 --> 00:21:38,066
There was an invite from
a TV show.

356
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:39,633
To me.

357
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:41,920
It was a personal request.

358
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,253
Which TV show?

359
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:46,620
Well, it's about the
Fourth Industrial Revolution,

360
00:21:46,700 --> 00:21:50,053
and I guess they want
input from a lawyer.

361
00:21:50,133 --> 00:21:53,453
But now that I think about it,
it's actually a big burden.

362
00:21:53,533 --> 00:21:54,820
As you all know,

363
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,753
I've no interest in
standing in the spotlight

364
00:21:56,833 --> 00:21:59,453
or becoming famous.
I'm the type who just

365
00:21:59,533 --> 00:22:02,320
quietly gives his best
in his given duties.

366
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:04,153
Right?

367
00:22:04,233 --> 00:22:06,486
But then, this director has been
begging me,

368
00:22:06,566 --> 00:22:09,253
and this is a chance to
promote Always.

369
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:10,786
So I decided to
just make the sacrifice

370
00:22:10,866 --> 00:22:14,020
and go on the show.

371
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:16,700
Hey, you already wrote about it
on your social media.

372
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:21,386
Hello, this is Yeon Jun-gyu
from Always.

373
00:22:21,466 --> 00:22:24,353
I'll be participating in
a debate TV show.

374
00:22:24,433 --> 00:22:26,586
It's to air on February 15th,
at 9 a.m.,

375
00:22:26,666 --> 00:22:28,033
and I'll see you all there!

376
00:22:36,666 --> 00:22:39,386
Anyway, it's a live show
at 9 a.m. tomorrow,

377
00:22:39,466 --> 00:22:41,020
and I just had a call from
the same director.

378
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:43,653
He says he'd like one more.

379
00:22:43,733 --> 00:22:45,220
So, we need one more.

380
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:46,486
Who do you think should join me?

381
00:22:46,566 --> 00:22:47,953
I think

382
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:50,086
it should be someone
who's not scared to

383
00:22:50,166 --> 00:22:52,086
express his opinions eloquently
on a live show,

384
00:22:52,166 --> 00:22:54,366
and with the looks, too.

385
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:57,366
So how about Mr. Kwon?

386
00:22:58,666 --> 00:23:00,486
Right? He's our
best choice, right?

387
00:23:00,566 --> 00:23:02,386
Then it's decided,

388
00:23:02,466 --> 00:23:04,453
you'll join me for the show
tomorrow morning.

389
00:23:04,533 --> 00:23:05,986
No, I refuse.

390
00:23:06,066 --> 00:23:07,520
I've a lot of work tomorrow.

391
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:10,020
If this is all there is,
then may I take my leave?

392
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:11,733
We need to go to Court now,
so get ready.

393
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,233
Sure.

394
00:23:13,966 --> 00:23:15,386
Oh man.

395
00:23:15,466 --> 00:23:17,986
Does he have to be so cold?

396
00:23:18,066 --> 00:23:20,953
Why can't he at least
refuse with a smile?

397
00:23:21,033 --> 00:23:24,020
It's not one or two days that
he's been like that.

398
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:25,620
Well...

399
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:28,286
I'm sure he still shows his smile
to people he want to show it to.

400
00:23:28,366 --> 00:23:31,253
And I'm sure he'll smile
when he's really happy.

401
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:32,966
For example, like...

402
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:39,820
Ah, forget what I said.

403
00:23:39,900 --> 00:23:41,300
Then please excuse me, too.

404
00:23:45,433 --> 00:23:47,220
Anyway, if Mr. Kwon isn't so keen,

405
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:48,820
then who should go instead?

406
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:51,520
Any volunteers between you two?

407
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:52,633
Me!

408
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,253
You both want to go?

409
00:23:56,333 --> 00:23:57,566
Put that hand down.

410
00:23:59,433 --> 00:24:01,466
Can you move your car?
You've parked illegally.

411
00:24:03,933 --> 00:24:07,420
So the next trial is
in two weeks, is it?

412
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:10,120
Yes, please re-confirm
the date and place.

413
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,253
Yes, sir!

414
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:12,333
Kwon Jung-rok!

415
00:24:13,433 --> 00:24:14,633
Yeo-reum.

416
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:17,700
Yeo-reum? Ah, that's right.

417
00:24:19,566 --> 00:24:20,520
You had a trial?

418
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:22,420
Yes. You're done with yours, too?

419
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:23,986
Yes. Great timing!

420
00:24:24,066 --> 00:24:26,400
How about you join me for
coffee if you're free?

421
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:30,766
Should I? I can spare
about 30 minutes.

422
00:24:31,633 --> 00:24:33,933
Hello. You must be Ms. Oh.

423
00:24:34,833 --> 00:24:36,620
How do you know me?

424
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:38,986
I just happened to hear about you.

425
00:24:39,066 --> 00:24:40,486
How about you join us for tea?

426
00:24:40,566 --> 00:24:41,566
Will that be okay?

427
00:24:42,633 --> 00:24:44,820
She's not so comfortable
with crowded...

428
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:46,453
No, it's alright.

429
00:24:46,533 --> 00:24:47,666
I'd like to come, too.

430
00:24:52,133 --> 00:24:54,086
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

431
00:24:54,166 --> 00:24:55,766
Then I'll leave you to it.

432
00:24:57,266 --> 00:24:59,153
Black for Ms. Oh and I,

433
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:01,333
and for you...
With milk and sugar, right?

434
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,553
That sweet tooth of yours...

435
00:25:04,633 --> 00:25:06,186
You won't even drink coffee
unless it's sweet.

436
00:25:06,266 --> 00:25:09,786
I don't understand people
who like it bitter.

437
00:25:09,866 --> 00:25:11,386
Sweet tooth?

438
00:25:11,466 --> 00:25:12,420
You didn't know?

439
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:15,366
He doesn't drink coffee
without sugar and milk.

440
00:25:18,366 --> 00:25:20,353
It's not just coffee.
There's also...

441
00:25:20,433 --> 00:25:21,666
That's enough, stop.

442
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:23,933
Should I, then?

443
00:25:25,766 --> 00:25:28,120
Oh, sorry to bring you here
without asking you first.

444
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:30,286
This is the only place I know of

445
00:25:30,366 --> 00:25:31,986
where you can chat quietly

446
00:25:32,066 --> 00:25:33,400
away from the crowd.

447
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,753
No, it's fine.

448
00:25:36,833 --> 00:25:38,566
I'm actually fine with anywhere.

449
00:25:39,066 --> 00:25:40,686
Actually, I know everything.

450
00:25:40,766 --> 00:25:42,120
Including your identity.

451
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,433
You're Oh Yoon-seo, right?

452
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:47,753
Don't tell me...

453
00:25:47,833 --> 00:25:49,020
It wasn't me.

454
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:50,653
I heard from Mr. Choi Yun-hyuk.

455
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:53,220
I bumped into him
at Court the other day.

456
00:25:53,300 --> 00:25:54,786
I see.

457
00:25:54,866 --> 00:25:56,786
So, how is it
working as a secretary?

458
00:25:56,866 --> 00:25:59,620
I bet it's hard because
Jung-rok's hard to deal with.

459
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:00,953
- Um...
- How?

460
00:26:01,033 --> 00:26:02,386
How?

461
00:26:02,466 --> 00:26:05,286
You’ve no idea
how cold you can be.

462
00:26:05,366 --> 00:26:07,700
Sometimes, I get really fed up.

463
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:10,953
What, I'm like that?

464
00:26:11,033 --> 00:26:12,033
Yes!

465
00:26:14,133 --> 00:26:18,453
You two must be close.

466
00:26:18,533 --> 00:26:20,700
We were always together
at college.

467
00:26:22,033 --> 00:26:23,300
What, just you two?

468
00:26:24,233 --> 00:26:25,233
Three, actually.

469
00:26:26,033 --> 00:26:27,720
Three, including Kim Se-won.

470
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:29,233
Kim Se-won?

471
00:26:30,666 --> 00:26:32,020
Let's all meet up sometime.

472
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:33,700
You can't avoid him forever.

473
00:26:34,566 --> 00:26:35,900
We're both busy.

474
00:26:36,566 --> 00:26:38,453
Hey, we should have
dinner sometime.

475
00:26:38,533 --> 00:26:40,553
It's been a long time
since we last did that.

476
00:26:40,633 --> 00:26:42,720
Sure, anytime's fine for me.

477
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:44,300
I'm going to be touched again.

478
00:26:46,533 --> 00:26:48,720
Sorry to leave you
out of the conversation.

479
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:51,233
Actually, you should join us
when we have dinner.

480
00:26:53,033 --> 00:26:55,300
Well... I'll see.

481
00:26:58,866 --> 00:27:01,653
Why aren't you wearing
your scarf? Aren't you cold?

482
00:27:01,733 --> 00:27:03,433
No, it's not so cold today.

483
00:27:04,266 --> 00:27:06,353
I see you don't get
so cold easily.

484
00:27:06,433 --> 00:27:08,666
No, that's why I like winter.

485
00:27:09,733 --> 00:27:12,166
What, not summer?
(Yeo-reum: "Summer" in Korean)

486
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:13,986
Pardon?

487
00:27:14,066 --> 00:27:15,100
It's nothing.

488
00:27:16,566 --> 00:27:18,486
As for that spell check
I asked you to do,

489
00:27:18,566 --> 00:27:20,086
I'd like it by 5 p.m.

490
00:27:20,166 --> 00:27:22,786
No, I'm going to
give it to you at 5:10 p.m.

491
00:27:22,866 --> 00:27:24,233
I'm a little tired, you see.

492
00:27:28,266 --> 00:27:29,533
By the way, Mr. Kwon.

493
00:27:30,700 --> 00:27:32,833
Why are you so loose
with your smiles?

494
00:27:35,100 --> 00:27:37,353
That's the first time
anyone's told me such a thing.

495
00:27:37,433 --> 00:27:40,353
But didn't you say it's nicer
when I smile?

496
00:27:40,433 --> 00:27:43,186
Well, too much of something
isn't always a good thing.

497
00:27:43,266 --> 00:27:44,253
And besides,

498
00:27:44,333 --> 00:27:46,533
I don't think a smile suits you.

499
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:50,000
I said, stop smiling!

500
00:27:55,533 --> 00:27:57,800
What... What's wrong with her?

501
00:28:00,300 --> 00:28:02,620
I really liked that restaurant
you took me to.

502
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:05,153
I should take my other
colleagues there next time.

503
00:28:05,233 --> 00:28:08,553
It won't be a secret find
if you tell just everyone.

504
00:28:08,633 --> 00:28:10,133
Maybe you're right.

505
00:28:11,333 --> 00:28:13,653
By the way, how is
Prosecutor Kim Se-won?

506
00:28:13,733 --> 00:28:14,920
What about him?

507
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,420
He's our branch's idol, isn't he?

508
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:19,753
There weren't just
one or two women

509
00:28:19,833 --> 00:28:22,120
who cried at the news of
his transfer 2 years ago.

510
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:26,600
By the way, do you think
he has a girlfriend?

511
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:30,266
No, he broke up with her
two years ago.

512
00:28:31,100 --> 00:28:32,453
How do you know?

513
00:28:32,533 --> 00:28:36,253
He and Prosecutor Yu were
pretty famous, didn't you know?

514
00:28:36,333 --> 00:28:38,186
You mean, Yu Yeo-reum?

515
00:28:38,266 --> 00:28:40,520
Yes. They were dating for
about 7 years,

516
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:43,233
then two years ago,
it ended completely!

517
00:28:44,666 --> 00:28:45,666
Why?

518
00:28:47,233 --> 00:28:48,300
Who knows.

519
00:28:49,633 --> 00:28:52,966
They say Prosecutor Yu isn't
all that nice, maybe that's why.

520
00:28:59,166 --> 00:29:00,233
Prosecutor Yu.

521
00:29:01,500 --> 00:29:03,100
Why do you look so scared?

522
00:29:04,633 --> 00:29:07,753
In case I bite,
since I'm not all that nice?

523
00:29:07,833 --> 00:29:10,620
I'm sorry.

524
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:12,720
It's alright, it's true.

